appendRecords() method (line 674) calls maybeAddDelayedProduce() (line 704) only when requiredAcks == -1.\n\n7. DELAYED PRODUCE DECISION (ReplicaManager.scala and DelayedProduce.scala): The delayedProduceRequestRequired() method (line 1355) checks if delayedProduceRequestRequired(requiredAcks, ...) returns true. This function returns true only when requiredAcks == -1 (line 1358). When true, maybeAddDelayedProduce() creates a DelayedProduce operation (line 919) with ProduceMetadata containing the requiredAcks value.\n\n8. REPLICA ACKNOWLEDGMENT CHECKING (DelayedProduce.scala and Partition.scala): The DelayedProduce operation's tryComplete() method (line 89) checks if pending acks are satisfied by calling partition.checkEnoughReplicasReachOffset() for each partition (line 101). This method (Partition.scala line 1089) checks if the high watermark >= required offset and validates that the minimum ISR requirement is met (lines 1111-1119). The operation completes when all in-sync replicas have acknowledged the write by reaching the required offset, or times out after the configured timeout period.\n\nIn summary:\n- acks=0: Producer doesn't wait for any acknowledgment; broker sends immediate response\n- acks=1: Producer waits for leader acknowledgment; broker sends response after leader appends records\n- acks=-1 (all): Producer and broker wait for all in-sync replicas to acknowledge via the DelayedProduce mechanism, checking replica log end offsets against the required offset"
